# .nomtu — The Atomic Dictionary Entry

**Each .nomtu is a word. Like a dictionary entry, not code.**

## What Is a .nomtu

A .nomtu is the smallest distributable unit in Nom.
It describes one concept with one contract in plain text.

    hash.nomtu = describes "hashing" — what it takes, gives, and costs
    store.nomtu = describes "storage" — what it takes, gives, and costs
    limiter.nomtu = describes "rate limiting"

A .nomtu does NOT contain implementation code.
It contains the MEANING of the word.
The implementation is stored separately in the registry.

## Structure

    word: hash
    describe: convert data into irreversible fixed-length string
              to protect passwords and verify integrity
    kind: crypto

    contract
    in: bytes
    out: hashbytes
    effects: cpu
    pre: in.length > 0
    post: irreversible and unique

    scores
    security: 0.96
    performance: 0.72
    quality: 0.91
    reliability: 0.95

    source: rustcrypto
    version: 3.2
    license: MIT
    tests: 847

    variants
    argon2: security=0.96 performance=0.72
    bcrypt: security=0.89 performance=0.81
    sha256: security=0.91 performance=0.95

## The Describe Field

Every .nomtu has a `describe` field — a sentence in plain English
that says what this word means. When the .nom compiler encounters
a phrase it doesn't recognize, it searches .nomtu descriptions
to find the best match.

    You write:  "need something to convert data into irreversible string"
    Compiler:   matches against hash.nomtu describe field
    Result:     selects hash.nomtu (85% match)

This is how dictionaries work — you look up words by meaning,
not just by name.

## Where .nomtu Lives

    nom.dev          the online registry (all .nomtu ever published)
    ~/.nom/nomtu/    local cache (downloaded on demand)
    ./nomtu/         project-local (custom words, escape hatch)

## Properties

    All text         readable, searchable, greppable, diffable
    Content-addressed hash of the file = unique identity
    One concept       one word per .nomtu (not thousands of functions)
    Scored           8-dimension quality metrics with evidence
    Provenanced      source repo, commit, license, tests
    Variants         multiple implementations ranked by score
    Composable       combine with other .nomtu via -> :: + operators
